I. 🧠 Core Definition

Embodied Tensor Interface (ETI):
A representation system where an entity (human, system, narrative, market) is modeled as a structured form, and its state is encoded via spatial, visual, and material modifications to that form over time.

ETI converts abstract data → geometric, inspectable state.

⸻

II. 🔑 Canonical Pattern

ETI:
  entity: structured representation (body, graph, object)
  state_encoding:
    location: where on structure
    modification: color | pin | deformation | attachment | intensity
    relation: connections between structures (threads/edges)
  time:
    delta_tracking: sequence of state changes
  interpretation:
    pattern_recognition: human + machine


