IV. 🧱 Invariants (Pantheon-Aligned)

1. Spatial Encoding Invariant
Meaning must map to position on structure.

2. Modification Invariant
State is expressed through change, not static labels.

3. Delta Invariant
Time is captured as transformation, not snapshots.

4. Interpretability Invariant
Human intuition must extract signal without translation.

5. Compression Invariant
High-dimensional state → low-dimensional structure.

6. Non-Coercion / Ethics Gate (≥0.7)
Representation must not mislead or manipulate interpretation.

